[<p class="sh2"><span>SIGN UP</span> FOR OUR NEWSLETTER</p>, <p>\u201cSince 2013, millions of people have turned to Vine to laugh at loops and see creativity unfold. <span class="markup--quote markup--p-quote is-other">Today, we are sharing the news that in the coming months we\u2019ll be discontinuing the mobile app,\u201d the company wrote i</span>n a blog post.</p>, <p class="sh2"><span>SIGN UP</span> FOR OUR NEWSLETTER</p>, <p>Although Twitter did not provide a reason for the decision, it comes at a time when the company is struggling, with the\xa0<a href="/web/20161028134133/http://www.breitbart.com/tech/2016/10/27/twitter-announces-layoffs-for-9-of-staff/">announcement this week</a> that it would cut 9% of its workforce.</p>, <p>The Vine service was acquired by Twitter in 2012 for $30 million, and has since operated as a separate\xa0service, allowing users to share six second clips which were most popularly used for humorous purposes.\xa0<a href="/web/20161028134133/http://expandedramblings.com/index.php/vine-statistics/">At its peak</a>, the platform had over 200 million monthly users.</p>, <p>However, the service has since struggled to compete against the likes of Instagram and Snapchat, who now dominate the video sharing market.</p>, <p>Twitter claims that the service will not be affected in the near future, adding that\xa0users will \u201cbe able to access and download your Vines\u201d for the time being.</p>, <p><em>You can follow Ben Kew <a class=" x5l x5l x5l" href="/web/20161028134133/https://www.facebook.com/benjkew/?skip_nax_wizard=true" rel="noopener" target="_blank">on Facebook</a>, on Twitter at </em><em><a class=" x5l x5l x5l" href="/web/20161028134133/https://twitter.com/ben_kew" rel="noopener" target="_blank">@ben_kew</a>,\xa0or\xa0email him at bkew@breitbart.com\xa0</em></p>]